All seven verification criteria were checked against the repo (code paths, archive directory, file existence, git diff). The taxonomy, H031 invariant, World Wire rename, Definition-era references, and archive prefixes in `current-architecture.md` are correct. The only substantive gap is incomplete cleanup in `README.md` (B1/B2 + I1), which is a completeness defect in an in-scope file, not a false claim. Fix the two blocking items and README.md joins the other six as safe authority.
